The paper deals with graph embedding problems, which are typically studied in the sub-fields of discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computational complexity (cs.CC), computational geometry (cs.CG), and graph theory (cs.GT). The use of parameterized complexity theory also suggests that cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) may be a relevant sub-category.
